SIMPLE: feeder
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Feeder
<hw>Feed"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, gives food or supplies nourishment; steward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A couple of friends, his chaplain and <qex>feeder</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who furnishes incentives; an encourager.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>feeder</xex> of my riots.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who eats or feeds; specifically, an animal to be
fed or fattened.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With eager feeding, food doth choke the <qex>feeder</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>One who fattens cattle for slaughter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A stream that flows into another body of water; a
tributary; specifically <fld>(Hydraulic Engin.)</fld>, a water course
which supplies a canal or reservoir by gravitation or natural
flow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>A branch railroad, stage line, air route, or the
like; a side line which increases the business of the main
line.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A small lateral
lode falling into the main lode or mineral vein.</def> <au>Ure.</au>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A strong discharge of gas from a fissure; a
blower.</def> <au>Raymond.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>8.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>An auxiliary part of a machine
which supplies or leads along the material operated upon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>9.</sn> <fld>(Steam Engine)</fld> <def>A device for supplying
steam boilers with water as needed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feeding</ent>⟦br⟧
